WEBVTT

00:02.043 --> 00:03.294
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...
 DIVORCE SUITS YOU.

00:03.294 --> 00:05.336
YOUR CHARMS WON'T
WORK ON ME, PASCAL.

00:05.336 --> 00:07.178
NOT THIS TIME.

00:07.178 --> 00:10.010
I HAVE NO INTENTION
OF MERGING OUR COMPANIES.

00:10.010 --> 00:13.184
WHAT IF I GOT YOU THE ONE THING
YOU'VE ALWAYS WANTED?

00:13.184 --> 00:15.936
I HAVE EVERYTHING A MAN
COULD WANT.

00:15.936 --> 00:17.558
EXCEPT VICTORIA.

00:17.558 --> 00:19.350
Javier: I SORT OF GAVE
MY PAROLE OFFICER YOUR ADDRESS.

00:19.350 --> 00:23.104
HE'S THIS MILLENNIAL
COMPUTER GENIUS FROM PRISON.

00:23.104 --> 00:25.196
I HAVE NO INTENTION
OF GOING ANYWHERE.

00:25.196 --> 00:27.108
YET THIS PROPERTY
BELONGS TO ME.

00:27.108 --> 00:29.990
IT'S TIME TO SHOW
OUR FATHERS WHAT WE'RE
CAPABLE OF. CARE TO JOIN ME?

00:29.990 --> 00:32.243
FAKING A PREGNANCY
TO FORCE DANIEL INTO MARRIAGE.

00:32.243 --> 00:34.535
YOUR DIRTY,
LITTLE SECRET IS OUT.

00:34.535 --> 00:36.207
Woman: MRS. GRAYSON!

00:36.207 --> 00:37.498
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]
 [ REPORTERS SHOUTING QUESTIONS ]

00:37.498 --> 00:39.039
I HAD TO CREATE A PUBLIC BREAK
FROM THE GRAYSONS.

00:39.039 --> 00:41.462
WHAT'S "TWM"? MY MOM SAID SHE
NEVER KNEW WHO WROTE THE LETTER.

00:41.462 --> 00:43.964
IT WAS EUROPEAN.
 PASCAL IS A PART OF THIS?

00:43.964 --> 00:45.256
YEAH, I THINK HE IS.

00:46.797 --> 00:51.172
Emily: ADDICTION --
AN IMPULSE THAT, ONCE INDULGED,

00:51.172 --> 00:54.385
IS IMPOSSIBLE TO PACIFY.

00:54.385 --> 00:58.269
EVEN WHEN STARVED,
 THE HUNGER SURVIVES.

00:58.269 --> 00:59.680
FIRST
THE DOLCE & GABBANA.

00:59.680 --> 01:02.103
AND NOW GEORGE DE LA TOUR'S
"THE FORTUNE TELLER"?

01:02.103 --> 01:03.234
IT'S YOUR FAVORITE, NO?

01:03.234 --> 01:05.105
AT THE MET
WHERE IT BELONGS.

01:05.105 --> 01:07.398
I THOUGHT YOU'D LIKE TO
ENJOY IT FOR A MONTH OR TWO.

01:07.398 --> 01:10.030
I CANNOT BE BOUGHT --
ESPECIALLY BY A MAN

01:10.030 --> 01:12.743
WHOSE REPUTATION FOR ROMANCE
IS RECKLESS.

01:12.743 --> 01:16.036
THE RESULT OF
A LIFETIME OF MISTAKES.

01:16.036 --> 01:18.829
YOU DON'T KNOW ME,
PASCAL.

01:18.829 --> 01:20.791
OR WHAT I WANT.

01:26.257 --> 01:28.259
[ SIGHS ]

01:40.311 --> 01:44.855
Aiden: A LOVE THAT WILL ALWAYS
 TRIUMPH OVER DARKNESS.

01:44.855 --> 01:47.858
A LOVE THAT I WOULD
 LAY DOWN MY LIFE FOR.

01:47.858 --> 01:52.863
AT LEAST YOU'VE MOVED ON
FROM THE NOTE TO...

01:52.863 --> 01:56.076
OTHER
UNSOLVABLE RIDDLES.

01:56.076 --> 01:57.448
HAVE YOU HEARD
FROM AIDEN?

01:57.448 --> 01:59.660
NO.
AND I DON'T EXPECT TO.

01:59.660 --> 02:01.332
HE'S HONORING
WHAT I WANTED.

02:01.332 --> 02:03.334
WELL, I'VE BEEN
TRYING TO DO THAT, TOO.

02:03.334 --> 02:05.876
I HACKED INTO
THE LeMARCHAL MAINFRAME,

02:05.876 --> 02:07.668
BUT WADING THROUGH
EVERY FILE

02:07.668 --> 02:09.669
OF EUROPE'S
LARGEST MEDIA CONGLOMERATE

02:09.669 --> 02:14.635
FOR THE LETTERS "TWM"
IS JUST GONNA TAKE EONS.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.557
IT DEFINITELY CAN'T BE
"THE WHITE-HAIRED MAN," RIGHT?

02:16.557 --> 02:20.351
IT FITS, BUT...
I AM PRETTY SURE THAT

02:20.351 --> 02:23.264
THAT NICKNAME
WAS A "NOL-RIGINAL."

02:23.264 --> 02:24.895
[ SIGHS ]

02:24.895 --> 02:26.437
WELL, I CAN'T
WAIT ANY LONGER.

02:26.437 --> 02:28.229
WHAT ARE YOU GONNA DO?

02:28.229 --> 02:30.651
THE LETTER'S NOT ENOUGH
TO INCRIMINATE THE GRAYSONS,

02:30.651 --> 02:33.033
BUT PASCAL HAS A PIECE
OF THE PUZZLE THAT I DON'T,

02:33.033 --> 02:34.275
AND THERE MAY BE MORE.

02:34.275 --> 02:37.238
SO IF I CAN GET CLOSE TO HIM,
GAIN ACCESS --

02:37.238 --> 02:41.242
THEN YOU CAN FINALLY
FINISH THE PUZZLE.

02:42.953 --> 02:45.336
HEY.

02:45.336 --> 02:48.249
HEY. WORKING HARD?

02:48.249 --> 02:50.050
THE "VOULEZ" GOSSIP
TIP LINE

02:50.050 --> 02:52.843
HAS PRETTY MUCH
BECOME A PASCAL TRACKER.

02:52.843 --> 02:55.256
DOES THAT MEAN EMILY'S
DROPPED OFF THE RADAR?

02:55.256 --> 02:58.429
YEAH.
SHE'S YESTERDAY'S NEWS.

02:58.429 --> 03:00.351
THOUGH I'LL NEVER FORGET
WHAT SHE DID TO YOU.

03:00.351 --> 03:02.763
TO US.

03:02.763 --> 03:04.765
EMILY LIED TO OUR
ENTIRE FAMILY, CHARLOTTE.

03:04.765 --> 03:05.936
INCLUDING YOU.

03:05.936 --> 03:08.479
YOU'D THINK
SHE'D JUST LEAVE TOWN,

03:08.479 --> 03:11.151
INSTEAD OF STAYING HERE AND
MAKING THINGS HARDER FOR YOU.

03:11.151 --> 03:13.153
WHICH IS WHY
WE'RE GONNA RETURN THE FAVOR

03:13.153 --> 03:15.115
AND GO AFTER HER FRIENDS.
 WE?

03:16.156 --> 03:19.780
I DON'T KNOW, DANIEL.
 NO, NO, NO, NO.
LOOK, LOOK, LOOK, LOOK.

03:19.780 --> 03:22.533
YOU HELPED ME FIGURE OUT
WHAT DAD WAS UP TO.

03:22.533 --> 03:25.916
NOW WE CAN PUT THOSE SKILLS
TO AN EVEN WORTHIER CAUSE.

03:27.828 --> 03:28.829
OKAY.

03:29.960 --> 03:32.333
BUT JACK ISN'T INVOLVED
IN ALL THIS.

03:32.333 --> 03:33.714
I WANT TO
KEEP IT THAT WAY.

03:33.714 --> 03:37.298
FINE.
PORTER'S OFF THE TABLE.

03:37.298 --> 03:40.220
OKAY.
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

03:40.220 --> 03:42.433
"FORMER HAMPTONS ROYAL
STEVIE GRAYSON

03:42.433 --> 03:44.054
"CREATED HER OWN DRAMA
AT THE OPERA

03:44.054 --> 03:46.226
"BY ARRIVING ON THE ARM
OF HER SECRET SON,

03:46.226 --> 03:50.811
LOCAL TAVERN OWNER JACK PORTER."

03:50.811 --> 03:54.405
IT'S A GREAT PHOTO
OF US.

03:54.405 --> 03:57.237
YOU'RE NOT UPSET?

03:57.237 --> 04:00.911
I ASSUMED YOU WANTED IT RELEASED
ON YOUR OWN TERMS.

04:00.911 --> 04:02.283
IT WAS.

04:03.494 --> 04:04.865
I TOLD THE PHOTOGRAPHER.

04:04.865 --> 04:08.078
I HAVE SEEN HOW SECRETS
ARE USED AS LEVERAGE.

04:08.078 --> 04:09.670
AND CONSIDERING YOU'RE ABOUT
TO OWN GRAYSON MANOR,

04:09.670 --> 04:10.871
THE LAST THING
I WANTED TO DO

04:10.871 --> 04:13.003
WAS GIVE CONRAD OR VICTORIA
ANY AMMO.

04:13.003 --> 04:14.795
I STILL CAN'T UNDERSTAND

04:14.795 --> 04:16.677
HOW YOU COULD
BE MARRIED TO THAT MONSTER.

04:16.677 --> 04:19.640
CONRAD WASN'T ALWAYS
SO TERRIBLE.

04:19.640 --> 04:22.683
WE MET ON A BLIND DATE.

04:22.683 --> 04:25.265
HE WAS SO RELAXED
AND CHARMING.

04:25.265 --> 04:28.349
WE ENDED UP
HAVING SUCH A GREAT TIME.

04:28.349 --> 04:29.730
WE WENT
TO THE AIRPORT AND --

04:29.730 --> 04:31.692
AND TOOK THE FIRST FLIGHT
TO ANYWHERE.

04:31.692 --> 04:33.484
YOU KNOW,
TRYING TO PICTURE HIM LIKE THAT

04:33.484 --> 04:35.105
IS NEARLY IMPOSSIBLE.

04:35.105 --> 04:38.319
[ CHUCKLES ]
NO, IT DIDN'T LAST LONG.

04:38.319 --> 04:40.280
BUT HE'S NOT
SOLELY TO BLAME.

04:40.280 --> 04:43.113
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DEFEND HIM.
 I'M NOT, JACK.

04:43.113 --> 04:46.327
YOU'VE NEVER
SEEN ME DRUNK.

04:46.327 --> 04:49.169
AND THANK GOD
YOU NEVER WILL.

04:54.335 --> 04:56.126
ALL I SAID WAS

04:56.126 --> 04:58.339
"THE FORTUNE TELLER"
IS HER FAVORITE PAINTING,

04:58.339 --> 05:00.471
AND YOU HAD IT DESIGNATED
ON LOAN TO HER?

05:00.471 --> 05:03.263
I THOUGHT YOU KNEW VICTORIA
BETTER THAN

05:03.263 --> 05:06.477
[Chuckling]
TO MAKE GRAND GESTURES.

05:06.477 --> 05:08.809
I THOUGHT YOU WERE A MAN
WHO COULD KEEP HIS PROMISES.

05:08.809 --> 05:11.191
I AM, BUT TO ERASE
YOUR SOILED PAST

05:11.191 --> 05:15.195
FROM VICTORIA'S MEMORY
REQUIRES A SLOW BURN.

05:15.195 --> 05:17.568
JUST GIVE IT TIME.

05:17.568 --> 05:19.149
WELL,
DON'T WASTE MINE.

05:19.149 --> 05:22.282
MAKE IT HAPPEN, OR YOU CAN
FORGET ABOUT OUR PARTNERSHIP.

05:22.282 --> 05:24.945
JUST RELAX, PASCAL.

05:24.945 --> 05:27.748
WE'LL BOTH GET
WHAT WE DESERVE.

05:30.080 --> 05:31.121
ANYTHING ELSE FOR YOU,
MONSIEUR LeMARCHAL?

05:31.121 --> 05:32.413
ANOTHER MONTECRISTO.

05:32.413 --> 05:35.005
MY APOLOGIES, SIR,
BUT WE JUST SOLD OUR LAST TWO.

05:35.005 --> 05:37.007
JE SERAIS HEUREUX
 DE PARTAGER.

05:38.589 --> 05:40.170
MRS. GRAYSON.

05:40.170 --> 05:42.172
OR SHOULD I SAY
MISS THORNE

05:42.172 --> 05:44.725
AFTER LAST WEEK'S EXCITEMENT
AT THE OPERA?

05:44.725 --> 05:47.347
EMILY IS FINE,
IF I MAY CALL YOU PASCAL.

05:49.349 --> 05:53.644
I'M AWARE THAT MANY OF MY
NEWS OUTLETS THRIVE ON SCANDAL,

05:53.644 --> 05:55.856
BUT I HAVE NO INTEREST
IN BECOMING ONE.

05:55.856 --> 05:58.479
WELL, THEN AT LEAST,
MAY I?

06:03.614 --> 06:05.866
MERCI.

06:11.201 --> 06:14.665
YOU AFTER A DISCHARGE,
SOLIDER?

06:14.665 --> 06:17.207
BECAUSE IT LOOKS LIKE

06:17.207 --> 06:19.259
YOU JUST SHOT YOURSELF
IN THE FOOT.

06:19.259 --> 06:21.301
NOT AT ALL.
 [ SNIFFS ]

06:21.301 --> 06:23.884
JUST CHANGED TACTICS.

06:25.846 --> 06:36.276
[ CHUCKLES ]

06:39.319 --> 06:40.441
[ LAUGHTER ]

06:40.441 --> 06:42.072
TO VICTORIA.

06:42.072 --> 06:44.865
BACK IN OUR MIDST
AND BACK ON THE MARKET.

06:44.865 --> 06:47.077
OH, I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT THAT.

06:47.077 --> 06:48.579
[ LAUGHTER ]
 PASCAL LeMARCHAL?

06:48.579 --> 06:50.451
HE WAS RATHER DASHING
AT THE OPERA.

06:50.451 --> 06:52.793
DIDN'T YOU TWO DATE
BEFORE CONRAD?

06:52.793 --> 06:55.125
IT'S A REGRETTABLE MISTAKE
OF MY YOUTH,

06:55.125 --> 06:58.038
ONE THAT I'M LOATHE TO REPEAT
OR DISCUSS.

06:58.038 --> 07:00.040
WELL, I WAS JUST HAPPY
TO HEAR THAT DANIEL

07:00.040 --> 07:02.463
HAS FINALLY BROKEN
HIS PATTERN WITH EMILY.

07:02.463 --> 07:04.384
[ SIGHS ]
 I STILL CANNOT BELIEVE

07:04.384 --> 07:07.047
THAT THAT GIRL
FAKED HER PREGNANCY.

07:07.047 --> 07:08.469
AND EVERYONE BELIEVED HER!

07:08.469 --> 07:10.140
[ SIGHS ]
EXCEPT YOU, VICTORIA.

07:10.140 --> 07:11.722
YOU WERE SUSPICIOUS
FROM THE ONSET.

07:11.722 --> 07:13.474
OH, I STILL AM.

07:13.474 --> 07:16.356
EMILY THORNE
IS A PLAGUE ON OUR HOMES.

07:16.356 --> 07:18.559
AND SINCE SHE SEEMS
DETERMINED TO STAY,

07:18.559 --> 07:21.151
I WOULD APPRECIATE
IF YOU WOULD ALL KEEP
AN EYE ON HER FOR ME.

07:21.151 --> 07:22.903
YOU CAN COUNT ON US.

07:22.903 --> 07:26.066
ANYONE WHO IS
AN ENEMY OF YOURS

07:26.066 --> 07:28.118
IS NOT LONG FOR THIS WORLD.

07:28.118 --> 07:30.871
[ LAUGHTER ]

07:30.871 --> 07:33.453
[ GASPS ]
OH, THERE'S ANOTHER ONE.

07:33.453 --> 07:34.665
EXCUSE ME.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.171
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

07:41.171 --> 07:42.583
OH, YOUR HOUSE?

07:42.583 --> 07:45.005
WELL, THIS PLACARD
I INTERCEPTED AT THE FRONT DOOR

07:45.005 --> 07:46.176
AUGURS OTHERWISE.

07:46.176 --> 07:47.848
STEVIE'S
NOT GONNA LET UP.

07:50.010 --> 07:51.391
NEITHER WILL I.

07:51.391 --> 07:52.803
WHY ARE YOU HERE,
CONRAD?

07:52.803 --> 07:56.016
YOU KNOW, I-I'D HEARD RUMORS
THAT THERE WAS A CERTAIN

07:56.016 --> 07:59.439
DE LA TOUR ORIGINAL
GRACING THE FOYER.

07:59.439 --> 08:02.362
IT'S A SHAMELESS VOLLEY
FROM PASCAL THAT I RETURNED.

08:02.362 --> 08:03.564
OH, GOOD.

08:03.564 --> 08:05.365
BECAUSE THE IDEA
OF YOU WITH THAT MAN

08:05.365 --> 08:06.527
MAKES MY BLOOD BOIL.

08:06.527 --> 08:07.988
WELL, THAT ALMOST
MAKES HIM APPEALING.

08:07.988 --> 08:09.660
HOWEVER, YOUR OPINION

08:09.660 --> 08:12.032
IS AS INAPPROPRIATE
AS THIS INTRUSION.

08:12.032 --> 08:14.665
I WOULD THINK YOU WOULD BE
BOTHERING YOUR FIRST EX-WIFE

08:14.665 --> 08:17.457
OVER HER RECENT
PUBLIC REVELATION.

08:17.457 --> 08:19.459
UM...

08:19.459 --> 08:21.752
REVELATION?
 OH, CONRAD.

08:21.752 --> 08:24.885
ALL THE MORNING NEWSPAPERS
YOU FLIP THROUGH,

08:24.885 --> 08:27.007
AND YOU ALWAYS SKIP
PAGE 6.

08:31.802 --> 08:34.014
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

08:38.808 --> 08:41.400
YOU SIZING UP
THE COMPETITION?

08:41.400 --> 08:42.982
NOT EXACTLY.

08:42.982 --> 08:45.405
THEY WANT ME TO BE
THEIR NEW EDITOR-IN-CHIEF.

08:45.405 --> 08:47.027
MM-HMM-HMM!

08:47.027 --> 08:49.029
IN ROME.

08:49.029 --> 08:52.032
WOW.
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:52.032 --> 08:54.615
I DIDN'T, UH --
DIDN'T KNOW

08:54.615 --> 08:56.416
THAT WAS SOMETHING
YOU WANTED.

08:56.416 --> 08:58.288
OH, NO, IT'S NOT.

08:58.288 --> 09:00.661
NO, I MEAN,
THIS IS AN AMAZING OPPORTUNITY.

09:00.661 --> 09:03.463
BUT ALL I REALLY WANT
IS "VOULEZ."

09:03.463 --> 09:04.965
AND YOU.

09:04.965 --> 09:07.758
THEN YOU'RE A LUCKY GIRL,
'CAUSE YOU'VE ALREADY GOT BOTH.

09:09.549 --> 09:13.133
WELL, THIS MAGAZINE
WILL NEVER BE MINE

09:13.133 --> 09:15.135
AS LONG AS MY FATHER
IS IN THE PICTURE.

09:15.135 --> 09:18.138
I GET IT, MARGAUX.
I DO.

09:18.138 --> 09:21.061
BUT [SIGHS] ROME?

09:21.061 --> 09:23.944
NO, I KNOW. I KNOW.

09:23.944 --> 09:26.947
THAT'S WHY
I WON'T TAKE IT.

09:26.947 --> 09:29.149
I LOVE YOU TOO MUCH.

09:29.149 --> 09:31.652
AND I CAN'T WAIT TO START THE
NEXT STEP OF OUR LIVES TOGETHER.

09:33.113 --> 09:35.746
WHAT?

09:35.746 --> 09:37.748
NO, I...

09:37.748 --> 09:40.540
I CAN'T LET YOU
JUST THROW THIS CHANCE AWAY.

09:40.540 --> 09:42.292
YOU NEED TO
SERIOUSLY CONSIDER IT.

09:42.292 --> 09:44.294
I DON'T KNOW.

09:44.294 --> 09:46.296
I DON'T KNOW.
THERE'S SO MUCH TO THINK ABOUT.

09:46.296 --> 09:49.299
BEING AWAY FROM YOU.
LEAVING ALL THIS.

09:49.299 --> 09:50.671
PASSING ON THE OPPORTUNITY

09:50.671 --> 09:52.633
TO FINALLY CUT TIES
WITH YOUR FATHER.

09:57.427 --> 09:59.599
ARE YOU SURE
WE COULD HANDLE THIS?

09:59.599 --> 10:01.682
NO.

10:01.682 --> 10:05.896
BUT...I KNOW
THAT I COULDN'T HANDLE

10:05.896 --> 10:08.108
KEEPING YOU FROM SOMETHING
THAT MIGHT MAKE YOU TRULY HAPPY.

10:08.108 --> 10:09.900
[ SMOOCHES ]

10:09.900 --> 10:11.732
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]
 [ SIGHS ]

10:11.732 --> 10:16.156
THOSE STICKY FINGERS OF YOURS
CERTAINLY PAID OFF.

10:16.156 --> 10:17.287
PASCAL'S COIN?

10:17.287 --> 10:19.910
IT'S A POKER CHIP

10:19.910 --> 10:23.704
FROM AN ULTRA-EXCLUSIVE TABLE
IN MACAU.

10:23.704 --> 10:26.206
THE BUY-IN
IS $1 MILLION.

10:26.206 --> 10:29.009
SO PASCAL'S
A GAMBLING MAN.

10:29.009 --> 10:30.841
I GUESS I'LL HAVE TO
EARN HIS RESPECT

10:30.841 --> 10:32.713
BY BEATING HIM
AT HIS OWN GAME.

10:32.713 --> 10:34.715
SO, WHAT'S NEXT?
 Woman: MY FAVORITE MOVIE IS
"ADVENTURES IN BABYSITTING."

10:34.715 --> 10:36.967
Javier: "ADVENTURES
IN BABYSITTING"? REALLY?

10:36.967 --> 10:39.890
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
WHAT ABOUT YOUR -- OH.

10:39.890 --> 10:43.223
...MOST EMBARRASSING
MOMENT EVER?

10:43.223 --> 10:44.895
I JUST GOT A CONTENDER.

10:44.895 --> 10:47.688
JAVIER,
MY WANNABE BESTIE,

10:47.688 --> 10:50.861
THIS IS EMILY,
MY ACTUAL BESTIE.

10:50.861 --> 10:53.613
ARE YOU TWO GONNA
HIT UP ATLANTIC CITY?

10:53.613 --> 10:55.946
I HAVE A NEW METHOD
TO BEAT ROULETTE

10:55.946 --> 10:58.038
I AM DYING TO TRY
RIGHT NOW.

10:58.038 --> 10:59.409
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU,
JAVIER.

10:59.409 --> 11:01.992
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER,
NOLAN.
 MM-HMM.

11:05.125 --> 11:07.167
WHAT IS THIS?

11:07.167 --> 11:09.960
A PROGRAM TO HIT ON GIRLS
WHILE YOU'RE UNDER HOUSE ARREST?

11:09.960 --> 11:12.923
NO. IT'S ACTUALLY A PROTOTYPE
OF WHAT I'M WORKING ON.

11:12.923 --> 11:15.135
SEE, IT BUILT
AN INTERACTIVE AVATAR

11:15.135 --> 11:16.717
BASED ON SOMEONE'S
SOCIAL-MEDIA PROFILE

11:16.717 --> 11:18.799
AND MY PREDICTIVE
LOGARITHMS.

11:18.799 --> 11:20.180
AND SINCE CHARLOTTE GRAYSON

11:20.180 --> 11:22.142
IS FAMOUS, SCANDALOUS,
AND PRETTY,

11:22.142 --> 11:24.935
SHE HAS QUITE THE
SIZE-6 FOOTPRINT TO WORK FROM.

11:24.935 --> 11:27.307
HMM.
 WATCH.

11:27.307 --> 11:30.150
CHARVATAR, HONEY, UM...

11:30.150 --> 11:32.402
WHICH NEIGHBOR DO YOU
HAVE THE MOST IN COMMON WITH?

11:32.402 --> 11:35.075
IT WAS EMILY.
 NOW IT'S YOU.

11:35.075 --> 11:37.117
OH. WELL, I SEE.

11:37.117 --> 11:39.319
IT'S A PROGRAM
DESIGNED TO INFLATE YOUR EGO.

11:39.319 --> 11:41.822
MM.
IT ONLY SPEAKS TRUTH.

11:44.995 --> 11:47.377
A HARVARD BUDDY OF MINE
IS THE PERFECT GUY

11:47.377 --> 11:49.589
TO HELP US
DEAL WITH YOUR FATHER.

11:49.589 --> 11:52.793
IT'S A BIT OF
A RISKY MOVE, BUT...

11:52.793 --> 11:54.965
YEAH, ACTUALLY,
DANIEL...

11:54.965 --> 11:57.217
I'VE CHANGED MY MIND.

11:57.217 --> 11:59.049
"VITO SPLENDIDO"
 MADE ME AN OFFER,

11:59.049 --> 12:00.430
AND I'M THINKING
ABOUT TAKING IT.

12:02.512 --> 12:04.104
HUH.

12:04.104 --> 12:07.267
WELL, I EXPECTED OTHER MAGAZINES
TO TRY AND POACH YOU.

12:07.267 --> 12:10.270
I JUST DIDN'T EXPECT YOU
TO GIVE UP SO QUICKLY.
 I'M NOT.

12:10.270 --> 12:12.903
I STARTED "VOULEZ"
 TO BREAK FREE FROM MY FATHER,

12:12.903 --> 12:14.484
BUT HE WON'T EVEN
LET ME HAVE THAT.

12:14.484 --> 12:17.237
MARGAUX, COME ON.
WE CAN PUSH HIM OUT.

12:17.237 --> 12:18.779
I'M SORRY, DANIEL.

12:18.779 --> 12:20.781
[ DOOR OPENS ]
 MY ONLY HESITATION
WAS LEAVING JACK,

12:20.781 --> 12:22.162
AND HE ENCOURAGED ME
TO GO.

12:22.162 --> 12:23.784
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

12:23.784 --> 12:26.126
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACH ]

12:26.126 --> 12:28.288
CHAR. COULD --
COULD YOU COME HERE A SEC?

12:28.288 --> 12:29.790
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

12:29.790 --> 12:32.082
I WAS JUST
TRYING TO REMEMBER.

12:32.082 --> 12:34.674
WHEN YOU MANAGED TO HELP EMILY
GET ALL HER MEMORY BACK,

12:34.674 --> 12:36.466
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

12:36.466 --> 12:38.718
I DIDN'T.
THAT WAS JACK, REMEMBER?

12:38.718 --> 12:40.510
OF COURSE.

12:40.510 --> 12:41.932
[ CHUCKLES ] MY BAD.

12:41.932 --> 12:45.055
AND H-HE ASKED YOU TO
SNEAK HIM IN HERE, TOO, RIGHT?

12:45.055 --> 12:46.386
WHAT ARE YOU GETTING AT?

12:46.386 --> 12:48.809
JUST THAT JACK
SEEMED TO PUT A LOT OF

12:48.809 --> 12:52.602
BEHIND-THE-SCENES EFFORT
INTO EMILY AFTER THE SHOOTING.

12:52.602 --> 12:55.025
YEAH.
HE'S HER FRIEND, DANIEL.
 IS THAT ALL?

12:55.025 --> 12:57.067
BECAUSE
I JUST THINK IT'S ODD

12:57.067 --> 12:58.698
THAT HE'S TRYING TO
PUSH YOU TO LEAVE

12:58.698 --> 13:00.070
NOW THAT EMILY'S SINGLE.

13:00.070 --> 13:02.702
DANIEL, STOP.
DON'T LISTEN TO HIM.

13:02.702 --> 13:04.074
YOU'RE TRYING TO
MANIPULATE ME.

13:04.074 --> 13:06.036
NO, I'M JUST TRYING TO
GET YOU TO OPEN YOUR EYES.

13:06.036 --> 13:10.170
JACK IS DOING EXACTLY
WHAT YOUR FATHER ALWAYS HAS --

13:10.170 --> 13:11.791
WHAT'S BEST FOR HIM.

13:11.791 --> 13:13.463
IT'S TIME TO DO
WHAT'S BEST FOR YOU.

13:16.967 --> 13:19.299
[ SIREN WAILS ]

13:19.299 --> 13:20.300
Pascal: MISS THORNE?

13:20.300 --> 13:21.761
PARDON
THE LATE INTRUSION,

13:21.761 --> 13:24.975
BUT I PREFER
THE INTIMACY OF HAND-DELIVERY.

13:24.975 --> 13:28.308
I WANTED TO INVITE YOU
TO AN EVENT THAT I'M
THROWING TOMORROW --

13:28.308 --> 13:32.272
A MONTE CARLO NIGHT
FOR CHARITY.

13:32.272 --> 13:34.104
I DOUBT
YOU'LL BE ABLE TO RESIST

13:34.104 --> 13:36.106
CONSIDERING
IT ALLOWS YOU TO INDULGE

13:36.106 --> 13:38.148
IN BOTH YOUR FAVORITE
VIRTUE AND VICE.

13:38.148 --> 13:40.280
LET'S SEE.

13:40.280 --> 13:43.073
ALL OF THE PROCEEDS
GO TO RECHERCHE D'UN REMèDE,

13:43.073 --> 13:45.785
OF WHICH YOU ARE
A FOUNDING MEMBER, NO?

13:45.785 --> 13:48.658
AND IT HAPPENS TO BE A CAUSE
THAT'S DEAR TO MY HEART.

13:48.658 --> 13:52.122
[ SIGHS ]
BECAUSE OF YOUR IMAGE ISSUES,

13:52.122 --> 13:55.125
I'M AFRAID
YOU'RE NOT THE BEST PERSON

13:55.125 --> 13:57.837
TO HELP ME
FIGHT CHILDHOOD LEUKEMIA.

13:57.837 --> 14:00.010
[ CHUCKLES ]

14:00.010 --> 14:02.632
WELL, THERE ARE TWO SIDES
TO EVERY STORY, PASCAL.

14:02.632 --> 14:06.266
AS THERE ARE TWO SIDES
TO EVERY COIN.

14:10.350 --> 14:13.353
SO YOU ARE A LIAR
 AND A THIEF?

14:13.353 --> 14:16.066
THERE'S SO MUCH ABOUT ME
YOU DON'T KNOW.

14:17.397 --> 14:19.439
COME TO THE PARTY,
AND YOU'LL FIND OUT.

14:21.982 --> 14:25.325
[ SCOFFS ]

14:30.200 --> 14:31.201
♪ THIS ONE WICKED ROAD ♪

14:31.201 --> 14:32.162
♪ YOU GONNA MAKE IT RIGHT ♪

14:32.162 --> 14:33.373
HEY.

14:33.373 --> 14:35.996
ANOTHER EX-MRS. GRAYSON.

14:35.996 --> 14:37.797
I'D SAY
"WELCOME TO THE CLUB,"

14:37.797 --> 14:40.300
BUT I DON'T CARE MUCH
FOR THE OTHER MEMBER.

14:40.300 --> 14:41.711
[ SIGHS ]

14:41.711 --> 14:43.503
SO, HOW DOES IT FEEL?

14:43.503 --> 14:45.095
[ SIGHS ]
LIBERATING.

14:45.095 --> 14:47.427
HMM.

14:47.427 --> 14:49.970
AND, UH, THANK YOU
FOR YOUR OLD FILES.

14:49.970 --> 14:53.223
I HOPE IT SPURS SOMETHING NEW
TO HELP CLEAR DAVID'S NAME.

14:53.223 --> 14:55.775
YOU LET ME KNOW
IF YOU NEED ANYTHING ELSE.

14:55.775 --> 14:58.778
WELL, ACTUALLY,
I WAS WONDERING

14:58.778 --> 15:01.191
WHAT YOU COULD TELL ME
ABOUT PASCAL LeMARCHAL?

15:01.191 --> 15:04.824
CONRAD AND HIM
SEEM TO HAVE QUITE A PAST.

15:04.824 --> 15:06.866
AND NOT JUST
IN BUSINESS.

15:06.866 --> 15:10.370
PASCAL ACTUALLY
DATED VICTORIA FIRST.

15:10.370 --> 15:13.203
I DON'T KNOW WHAT HAPPENED,
BUT WHEN I GOT OUT OF REHAB,

15:13.203 --> 15:17.207
SHE WAS WITH CONRAD,
AND PASCAL WAS HISTORY.

15:17.207 --> 15:19.299
HMM. SO WAS I.

15:19.299 --> 15:20.210
HUH.

15:20.210 --> 15:22.042
LOOK WHO'S HERE.

15:22.042 --> 15:24.844
THERE'S MY BIG BOY.

15:24.844 --> 15:26.346
YOU WANT TO GO
LOOK AT THE BOATS?

15:26.346 --> 15:28.758
LET'S GO
LOOK AT THE BOATS.
 YEAH. THAT SOUNDS FUN.

15:28.758 --> 15:30.010
EMILY, EXCUSE US.

15:30.010 --> 15:31.972
YEAH, OF COURSE.

15:31.972 --> 15:34.554
[ SIGHS ]

15:34.554 --> 15:36.556
YOU OKAY?

15:36.556 --> 15:38.518
YEAH.

15:38.518 --> 15:40.150
[ CHUCKLES ]

15:40.150 --> 15:42.152
EXCEPT MARGAUX
WAS OFFERED A JOB IN ITALY.

15:42.152 --> 15:45.865
IT KILLED ME,
BUT I ENCOURAGED HER TO TAKE IT.

15:45.865 --> 15:47.657
IT'S WHAT'S BEST
FOR HER RIGHT NOW.

15:47.657 --> 15:50.330
DOES THAT MEAN THAT
YOU'RE LEAVING, TOO?

15:50.330 --> 15:53.833
WE HAVEN'T DISCUSSED IT YET.
MAYBE.

15:53.833 --> 15:55.835
I -- THOUGH I AM
BUYING THIS HOUSE,

15:55.835 --> 15:57.877
SO IT'LL BE LONG DISTANCE
FOR AWHILE.

15:57.877 --> 16:00.080
[ SIGHS ]

16:00.080 --> 16:02.252
GUESS I'M
JOINING THE CLUB, HUH?

16:04.294 --> 16:06.296
UH...

16:06.296 --> 16:08.388
ACTUALLY,
I ENDED THINGS WITH AIDEN.

16:10.140 --> 16:13.093
YOU WERE READY TO SPEND
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE WITH HIM.

16:13.093 --> 16:15.475
WHAT -- WHAT CHANGED?

16:15.475 --> 16:17.687
I DID.
[ SIGHS ]

16:17.687 --> 16:18.808
I GUESS.

16:20.100 --> 16:23.943
I WAS GOING THROUGH A LOT.
TOO MUCH.

16:23.943 --> 16:26.106
AND, OF COURSE,
I PUSHED HIM AWAY.

16:26.106 --> 16:28.158
EVEN THOUGH
YOU STILL LOVE HIM?

16:28.158 --> 16:30.240
[ SIGHS ]

16:33.113 --> 16:35.115
IF YOU WANT TO BE HAPPY
WHEN THIS IS ALL OVER,

16:35.115 --> 16:39.169
YOU NEED TO TELL HIM.
 I CAN'T.

16:39.169 --> 16:43.043
THE EMILY THORNE THAT I KNOW
CAN DO ANYTHING.

16:48.128 --> 16:50.840
THANKS.

16:50.840 --> 16:53.093
DANIEL, PLEASE!
CHARLES HAYWORTH?

16:53.093 --> 16:55.515
THAT WOULD BE LIKE DATING
YOUR FATHER ALL OVER AGAIN.

16:55.515 --> 16:56.726
YOU'RE THE ONE
WHO STAYED MARRIED

16:56.726 --> 16:58.138
TO THE GUY
FOR 25 YEARS.

16:58.138 --> 16:59.899
AND LOOK HOW WELL
THAT TURNED OUT.

16:59.899 --> 17:03.353
YOU HAVE TO ADMIT, YOU DID
BUILD AN EMPIRE TOGETHER.

17:03.353 --> 17:04.773
WELL, WHICH SEEMED IMPORTANT
WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE,

17:04.773 --> 17:06.695
BUT IT'S THE LAST THING
I'M LOOKING FOR IN A MAN NOW.

17:06.695 --> 17:08.318
YEAH? WHAT ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR, THEN?

17:08.318 --> 17:11.320
UH...
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:11.320 --> 17:13.532
SOMEONE WHO WOULD
TAKE THE TIME TO UNDERSTAND ME.

17:13.532 --> 17:16.366
WELL, THAT'S NO EASY FEAT.
 AND IT SHOULDN'T BE. COME ON.

17:16.366 --> 17:19.579
I HEARD PASCAL MADE
A LITTLE PLAY FOR YOU EARLIER.

17:19.579 --> 17:22.001
WELL,
HE HAS MUCH TO LEARN

17:22.001 --> 17:23.623
IF HE EVER HOPES
TO WIN ME BACK.

17:23.623 --> 17:26.626
I'M SORRY. "BACK"?

17:26.626 --> 17:29.299
YOU TWO DATED? HOW DID
I NEVER HEAR ABOUT THIS?

17:29.299 --> 17:31.881
DID YOU EVER REALLY
WANT TO KNOW ABOUT YOUR
MOTHER'S DATING HISTORY?

17:31.881 --> 17:34.514
GOD, NO, BUT PASCAL?

17:34.514 --> 17:36.096
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:36.096 --> 17:39.519
OH, WELL, BY THE TIME
I WENT TO PARIS ON SCHOLARSHIP,

17:39.519 --> 17:41.771
I WAS 16,
AND I HAD NO ONE THEN.

17:41.771 --> 17:44.144
WE MET AT THE FLEA MARKET,
BELIEVE IT NOT.

17:44.144 --> 17:46.316
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE WAS WORKING A BOOTH THERE.

17:46.316 --> 17:49.109
AND, UM...

17:49.109 --> 17:52.152
THERE WAS JUST
SOMETHING ABOUT HIM.

17:52.152 --> 17:54.614
WE WERE CRAZY
ABOUT EACH OTHER.

17:54.614 --> 17:57.697
PASCAL
TAUGHT ME HOW TO TRUST.

17:57.697 --> 18:00.250
AND? WHAT HAPPENED?

18:00.250 --> 18:02.041
WELL, MY VISA
WAS ONLY TEMPORARY,

18:02.041 --> 18:03.833
AND I HAD TO
RETURN TO NEW YORK.

18:03.833 --> 18:08.047
IT SEEMED LIKE THE END OF THE
WORLD TO BOTH OF US AT THE TIME.

18:08.047 --> 18:10.300
HE SENT ME AN ORCHID
FOR EVERY DAY WE WERE APART.

18:10.300 --> 18:12.342
WELL, HE MUST HAVE
BEEN SMITTEN.

18:12.342 --> 18:15.345
HMM, OR HE WAS
ASSUAGING HIS GUILT.

18:15.345 --> 18:17.347
I FLEW TO PARIS
TO SURPRISE HIM,

18:17.347 --> 18:19.098
AND I CAUGHT HIM
WITH ANOTHER WOMAN.

18:19.098 --> 18:21.100
AH.
 [ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

18:21.100 --> 18:23.223
THAT'S WHY YOU DON'T WANT TO
DEAL WITH HIM NOW.

18:23.223 --> 18:25.024
WELL, WE ALL MAKE MISTAKES
IN OUR YOUTH.

18:25.024 --> 18:27.227
[ SCOFFS ]
DON'T I KNOW IT.

18:27.227 --> 18:30.230
LOOKS LIKE EMILY'S
MAKING HER NEXT MOVE.

18:30.230 --> 18:32.232
SHE'S HOSTING AN EVENT
TOMORROW NIGHT.

18:32.232 --> 18:34.284
THIS IS
FOR PASCAL'S CHARITY.

18:34.284 --> 18:36.366
NOW, WHAT DO YOU SUPPOSE
SHE WANTS WITH HIM?

18:36.366 --> 18:38.538
THERE'S ONLY ONE WAY
TO FIND OUT.

18:40.370 --> 18:42.372
[ TROPICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

18:49.549 --> 18:51.341
WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

18:51.341 --> 18:53.553
THANKS, BUDDY.
 YEAH.

18:53.553 --> 18:56.756
I, UH -- I WAITED AT YOUR PLACE
FOR A LITTLE WHILE.

18:56.756 --> 18:59.179
YOUR NEIGHBOR SAID THAT
I COULD PROBABLY FIND YOU HERE.

18:59.179 --> 19:00.350
MM.

19:00.350 --> 19:02.262
HE WAS NICE.

19:02.262 --> 19:05.685
YEAH, WELL,
PEOPLE ARE HAPPY HERE, EMILY.

19:05.685 --> 19:07.267
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

19:07.267 --> 19:10.690
[ SIGHS ]

19:10.690 --> 19:14.534
WELL, I THOUGHT THAT MAYBE
YOU'D HAVE SOME INSIGHT.

19:14.534 --> 19:17.156
INSIGHT?

19:17.156 --> 19:18.738
OKAY.

19:18.738 --> 19:21.331
SO YOU --
YOU BROKE OUR AGREEMENT,

19:21.331 --> 19:22.952
YOU TRACKED ME DOWN,

19:22.952 --> 19:26.956
YOU FLEW ALL THE WAY OUT HERE
TO BERMUDA FOR INSIGHT?

19:30.089 --> 19:31.921
CAN'T YOU JUST ADMIT
THAT YOU CAME TO SEE ME?

19:31.921 --> 19:33.713
SO, I WANTED TO SEE YOU.
I'M SORRY.

19:33.713 --> 19:34.924
MAYBE I SHOULDN'T
HAVE COME.

19:36.426 --> 19:38.718
I MISS YOU.

19:38.718 --> 19:42.302
WELL, THAT'S WHAT HAPPENS
WHEN PEOPLE PART.

19:42.302 --> 19:43.973
IT'S --
IT'S CALLED MOVING ON.

19:43.973 --> 19:46.356
AIDEN,
CAN'T YOU JUST HEAR ME OUT?

19:46.356 --> 19:48.067
I WASN'T MYSELF.
YOU KNOW THAT.

19:48.067 --> 19:49.649
AND I'M NOT NOLAN.

19:49.649 --> 19:51.861
YOU CAN'T JUST
GIVE ME THE COLD SHOULDER

19:51.861 --> 19:55.074
AND EXPECT ME TO COME RUNNING
TO SAVE YOU THE NEXT DAY.

19:56.776 --> 20:00.910
ALL RIGHT? I'VE DONE
ALL I CAN FOR YOU.

20:00.910 --> 20:04.454
WE'RE ON OUR OWN
FROM NOW ON.

20:16.796 --> 20:18.598
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

20:20.760 --> 20:22.722
MARGAUX!

20:29.729 --> 20:32.772
I JUST SPENT TWO HOURS
WITH AN INTERPOL AGENT.

20:32.772 --> 20:34.734
HE RECEIVED
AN ANONYMOUS TIP

20:34.734 --> 20:36.906
THAT I WAS USING "VOULEZ"
 AS A TAX SHELTER!

20:36.906 --> 20:38.698
I CAN SEE
HOW THAT MIGHT BE A PROBLEM,

20:38.698 --> 20:39.739
SINCE IT'S ILLEGAL.

20:39.739 --> 20:41.160
DO YOU REALIZE THE DAMAGE

20:41.160 --> 20:43.573
AN INVESTIGATION LIKE THAT
WILL DO? HUH?

20:43.573 --> 20:45.915
NOT ONLY TO ME,
BUT ALSO TO YOU!

20:45.915 --> 20:47.957
ME?
[ CHUCKLES ]

20:47.957 --> 20:51.831
I AM JUST THE SILLY DAUGHTER
OF THE GREAT PASCAL LeMARCHAL.

20:51.831 --> 20:55.295
WHO COULD BELIEVE I WAS INVOLVED
IN SUCH DEVIOUS PLANS?

20:56.676 --> 20:59.138
NOW, AS IT TURNS OUT,

20:59.138 --> 21:03.723
DANIEL GRAYSON IS A FRIEND
OF THE INTERPOL AGENT.

21:03.723 --> 21:09.769
AND WE WOULD BE QUITE HAPPY
TO MAKE YOUR PROBLEM GO AWAY...

21:09.769 --> 21:12.732
IF YOU GIVE ME
WHAT I WANT.

21:16.356 --> 21:18.157
WHEN I ARRIVED HERE,
I WAS WORRIED

21:18.157 --> 21:20.279
FOR MY LITTLE GIRL
SWIMMING WITH THE SHARKS.

21:22.572 --> 21:23.783
NOW...

21:23.783 --> 21:26.956
I'M MORE WORRIED
FOR THE SHARKS.

21:35.254 --> 21:37.547
"VOULEZ" IS YOURS.
I'M OUT.

21:37.547 --> 21:39.509
AND CONRAD, TOO.

21:41.010 --> 21:43.803
HE WAS THE ONLY REASON
FOR YOUR VISIT, AFTER ALL.

21:43.803 --> 21:46.386
NOT THE ONLY REASON.

21:50.890 --> 21:52.311
[ DOOR OPENS ]

21:52.311 --> 21:53.693
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

21:53.693 --> 21:56.896
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

21:56.896 --> 21:58.858
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

22:05.535 --> 22:07.497
[ SIGHS ]

22:07.497 --> 22:09.829
WELL, I HOPE
I'M NOT INTERRUPTING.

22:09.829 --> 22:12.251
JUST FILLING OUT
THE FINAL PAPERWORK

22:12.251 --> 22:14.123
TO MAKE YOUR OLD HOUSE
MY NEW ONE.

22:14.123 --> 22:16.376
[ SIGHS ]

22:16.376 --> 22:17.877
ARE YOU DRUNK?

22:17.877 --> 22:20.049
I'M FINE.

22:20.049 --> 22:23.463
I HEARD YOUR OTHER NEWS.
ABOUT JACK.

22:23.463 --> 22:24.674
IS IT TRUE?

22:24.674 --> 22:26.846
IT IS.

22:26.846 --> 22:30.139
IT HITS HARDER
THAN I EXPECTED.

22:30.139 --> 22:32.351
YOU KNOW, AT FIRST,
I THOUGHT...

22:32.351 --> 22:35.144
"IS HE MINE?"

22:35.144 --> 22:37.737
BUT THEN I REMEMBERED THAT
BY THE TIME YOU GOT TO REHAB,

22:37.737 --> 22:39.689
WE WERE ALREADY
SLEEPING IN SEPARATE PLACES.

22:39.689 --> 22:41.651
ME IN OUR BEDROOM,
AND YOU

22:41.651 --> 22:44.654
WHEREVER YOU HAPPENED TO
PASS OUT THAT NIGHT.

22:44.654 --> 22:47.907
THE PAIN THAT I FELT...

22:47.907 --> 22:51.541
LEAVE IT TO CONRAD GRAYSON
TO MAKE MY ADDICTION

22:51.541 --> 22:54.754
AND UNPLANNED PREGNANCY
ABOUT HIM.

22:54.754 --> 22:56.756
IT HAPPENED
WHILE WE WERE MARRIED.

22:56.756 --> 22:58.958
TO THINK THAT
I'D BE UNAFFECTED IS NAIVE.

22:58.958 --> 23:01.671
JUST AS NAIVE AS BLAMING ME
SOLELY FOR OUR DIVORCE.

23:01.671 --> 23:03.883
I HAVE NEVER DONE THAT.

23:03.883 --> 23:06.716
NO, WE SHARE THE BLAME
FOR WHAT WE BECAME.

23:06.716 --> 23:08.508
BUT I NEVER SUSPECTED

23:08.508 --> 23:10.099
THE STOWAWAY WAS ANYTHING
BUT A REFUGE,

23:10.099 --> 23:13.723
BUT TO HEAR THAT YOU...
HAD A CHILD...

23:15.354 --> 23:18.648
...WITH ANOTHER
WHILE WE WERE MARRIED?
 CONRAD...

23:18.648 --> 23:20.820
COME ON. WE PLANNED
ON HAVING CHILDREN OF
OUR OWN, AND YOU...

23:22.782 --> 23:26.365
WELL, IT'S ABUNDANTLY CLEAR
WHY YOU DIDN'T COME TO ME

23:26.365 --> 23:28.618
TO MAKE AMENDS
DURING YOUR 12 STEPS,

23:28.618 --> 23:32.411
BUT THAT DOESN'T
EXCUSE THE LIE.

23:32.411 --> 23:34.243
I WAS YOUR HUSBAND.

23:36.205 --> 23:38.417
I DESERVED TO KNOW.

23:38.417 --> 23:40.750
YOU'RE RIGHT.

23:46.966 --> 23:48.468
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

23:48.468 --> 23:50.049
♪ LET'S GET AWAY ♪

23:50.049 --> 23:51.851
♪ LET'S GET AWAY ♪

23:51.851 --> 23:54.053
♪ JUST YOU AND ME ♪

23:54.053 --> 23:56.265
HAS MR. LeMARCHAL
ARRIVED YET?

23:56.265 --> 23:57.436
♪ LET'S GET AWAY ♪

23:57.436 --> 23:59.438
YOU JUST
HAD TO WEAR RED.

23:59.438 --> 24:02.231
I GUESS I'LL BE
BETTING ON BLACK FOR THE NIGHT.

24:02.231 --> 24:03.733
I'M SURPRISED YOU'LL BE
BETTING ON ANYTHING,

24:03.733 --> 24:05.865
SEEING AS I LEFT THE NAME
"GRAYSON" OFF THE GUEST LIST.

24:05.865 --> 24:07.156
OH, HONEY,
I DON'T NEED GUEST LISTS.

24:07.156 --> 24:08.618
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

24:08.618 --> 24:10.530
OR HAVE YOU ALREADY FORGOTTEN
THE DOORS I OPENED FOR YOU?

24:10.530 --> 24:12.331
YOU WERE A NOBODY
BEFORE ME.

24:12.331 --> 24:14.874
QUITE THE TURNOUT FOR
AN EVENT HOSTED BY A NOBODY.

24:14.874 --> 24:16.916
[ SCOFFS ] TRUST ME --
PEOPLE ARE ONLY HERE

24:16.916 --> 24:18.417
TO SEE THE CAR WRECK
THAT YOU'VE BECOME.

24:18.417 --> 24:20.840
[ CHUCKLES ]
 ONCE THE BLOOD
IS HOSED OFF THE PAVEMENT,

24:20.840 --> 24:21.961
THEY'LL BE ON THEIR WAY.

24:21.961 --> 24:24.504
HOW DID YOU
AFFORD ALL OF THIS, ANYWAY?

24:24.504 --> 24:27.507
THANK YOU
FOR REMINDING ME.

24:27.507 --> 24:29.468
IN ALL THE DRAMA
OF THE DIVORCE,

24:29.468 --> 24:31.470
I FORGOT TO RETURN THIS.

24:31.470 --> 24:33.472
MARGAUX, HI.

24:33.472 --> 24:35.054
EMILY.

24:35.054 --> 24:41.060
DANIEL, COME.
WE SHOULD BE CELEBRATING.

24:41.060 --> 24:42.311
YEAH.

24:42.311 --> 24:44.904
[ SIGHS ]

24:44.904 --> 24:47.987
YOU INVITED YOUR EX?
AWKWARD.

24:47.987 --> 24:50.700
OF COURSE I DIDN'T.
HIS ARROGANCE IS UNMATCHED.

24:50.700 --> 24:53.533
WELL, EXCEPT, OF COURSE,
BY THE FRENCH.

24:53.533 --> 24:55.164
SPEAK OF LE DIABLE...

24:55.164 --> 24:57.707
YOU'VE CLEARLY
CAUGHT HIS EYE.

24:57.707 --> 25:01.831
PROVE YOU CAN PLAY AT HIS LEVEL,
AND YOU'LL HAVE HIS EAR.

25:01.831 --> 25:05.004
TIME TO ANTE UP.

25:29.909 --> 25:32.111
WHAT IS GOING ON
BETWEEN YOU AND EMILY THORNE?

25:32.111 --> 25:33.913
I HAD NO IDEA

25:33.913 --> 25:35.745
IT WOULD TAKE JEALOUSY
TO GET YOUR ATTENTION.

25:35.745 --> 25:38.157
I AM TRYING TO HELP YOU,
AS I KNOW YOUR PROCLIVITY

25:38.157 --> 25:40.830
IS TO CHASE THE FIRST SKIRT
THAT FLARES AT YOU.

25:40.830 --> 25:43.212
CAN'T WE MOVE ON?

25:43.212 --> 25:44.794
YES,
LET'S STAY IN THE PRESENT.

25:44.794 --> 25:47.166
EMILY IS PLAYING YOU
LIKE SHE PLAYED MY SON.

25:47.166 --> 25:49.929
BUT I'M NOT YOUR SON.

25:49.929 --> 25:51.721
PASCAL, THERE YOU ARE.

25:51.721 --> 25:54.053
VICTORIA.
 EMILY.

25:54.053 --> 25:57.266
I'VE RESERVED A HIGH-STAKES
TABLE FOR THE TWO OF US.

25:57.266 --> 25:58.267
CARE TO JOIN ME?

25:58.267 --> 26:00.850
VERY TEMPTING.

26:00.850 --> 26:02.982
BUT I HAD A DIFFERENT OPPONENT
IN MIND TONIGHT.

26:04.143 --> 26:06.776
TRY YOUR HAND AT POKER?

26:06.776 --> 26:09.819
I WOULD LOVE TO.
 GREAT.

26:09.819 --> 26:11.821
EMILY...

26:11.821 --> 26:14.824
I'VE FOUND YOU
SOMEONE YOU CAN COMPETE WITH.

26:14.824 --> 26:18.077
SHALL WE?

26:25.625 --> 26:27.967
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

26:27.967 --> 26:30.169
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
YEAH, LET ME GET, UH...

26:30.169 --> 26:31.470
[ SNIFFS ]
...SOME ON 8...

26:31.470 --> 26:37.266
22, 19, 9, AND 4.

26:37.266 --> 26:39.428
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU JUST BET MY BIRTHDAY.

26:39.428 --> 26:42.061
NO KIDDING.
YOU'RE A LEO?

26:42.061 --> 26:44.353
NEXT
YOU'RE GONNA TELL ME

26:44.353 --> 26:46.936
THAT YOU LOVE
'80s TEEN MOVIES AND SASHIMI.

26:46.936 --> 26:50.439
I'M CHARLOTTE.
 JAVIER.

26:50.439 --> 26:52.151
WHY HAVEN'T I SEEN YOU
AROUND BEFORE, JAVIER?

26:52.151 --> 26:55.785
I JUST MOVED HERE. SPENT
THE LAST COUPLE YEARS UPSTATE.

26:55.785 --> 26:56.786
COLLEGE?

26:56.786 --> 26:58.738
PRISON.

26:58.738 --> 27:00.409
OOH.

27:00.409 --> 27:02.241
SHOULD I
NOT HAVE SAID THAT?

27:02.241 --> 27:04.583
NO, I'M GLAD YOU DID.

27:04.583 --> 27:06.415
YOUR HONESTY
IS REFRESHING.

27:06.415 --> 27:10.419
AS IS YOUR ATTITUDE
TOWARDS EX-CONS.

27:10.419 --> 27:12.591
HOW ABOUT YOU LET ONE
BUY YOU A DRINK?

27:12.591 --> 27:16.515
I WOULD, BUT THE POWERS THAT BE
WON'T LET ME HAVE ONE.

27:16.515 --> 27:19.889
JAVIER? A WORD?

27:22.391 --> 27:24.393
SO...

27:27.316 --> 27:29.478
...YOU TWEAKED
THE TRANSMITTER.

27:29.478 --> 27:31.901
YOU DID SAY I WAS GENIUS.
 NO, NO.

27:31.901 --> 27:34.533
CORRECTION.
I SAID YOUR PROGRAM WAS GENIUS.

27:34.533 --> 27:37.907
YOU, ON THE OTHER HAND,
ARE PROVING EXCEEDINGLY STUPID.

27:37.907 --> 27:40.579
MY GOD, TO THINK I WAS ACTUALLY
CONSIDERING A PARTNERSHIP.

27:40.579 --> 27:43.542
HOLD UP. ARE YOU SERIOUS?
 I WAS.

27:43.542 --> 27:44.744
BUT, I MEAN,
THIS LITTLE STUNT

27:44.744 --> 27:46.375
IS MAKING IT
VERY HARD TO TRUST YOU.

27:46.375 --> 27:48.417
I WILL STAY PUT FROM NOW ON.
PROMISE.

27:48.417 --> 27:50.840
JUST GIVE ME ONE --
ONE SECOND. ONE.

27:50.840 --> 27:53.252
♪ WHO'S JUST OUT OF SCHOOL ♪

27:53.252 --> 27:55.424
♪ THE THINGS THAT I SAY ♪

27:55.424 --> 27:58.257
♪ MAKE ME SOUND LIKE A BOY ♪
 [ CLEARS THROAT ]

27:58.257 --> 28:00.679
SO, UH, I GOT TO RUN.

28:00.679 --> 28:03.432
BUT INSTEAD
OF THAT DRINK,

28:03.432 --> 28:06.015
HOW ABOUT
I JUST DO YOU ONE BETTER.

28:06.015 --> 28:09.398
♪ SWEET WORDS
 WHEN YOU WANT TO HEAR ♪

28:09.398 --> 28:14.023
♪ NOW THOSE SAME SWEET WORDS
 ARE LOST IN MY EAR ♪
 SEE YOU AROUND, NEIGHBOR.

28:14.023 --> 28:16.235
♪ I JUST STAND AROUND
 WITH MY HEART FEELING SORE ♪
 Woman: WINNER -- 22!

28:16.235 --> 28:17.696
WAIT. YOU WON.

28:17.696 --> 28:20.319
DON'T I KNOW IT.

28:20.319 --> 28:22.701
Man: 6. COMING UP 6.

28:22.701 --> 28:23.913
COMING UP 6. COMING UP.

28:23.913 --> 28:27.086
[ CHEERING ]
 OH!

28:27.086 --> 28:28.087
YES! PAY ME.

28:28.087 --> 28:30.669
[ ALL CHEERING ]

28:32.381 --> 28:33.963
ALL RIGHT!

28:33.963 --> 28:35.464
[ LAUGHTER ]

28:35.464 --> 28:38.047
GOOD JOB. GOOD JOB.

28:38.047 --> 28:39.218
JACK!

28:40.469 --> 28:42.842
I FORCED MY FATHER
OUT OF "VOULEZ."

28:42.842 --> 28:45.514
IT'S ALL MINE.
 THAT'S GREAT!

28:45.514 --> 28:47.556
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT YOU WANTED.
H-HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

28:47.556 --> 28:49.398
WELL, DANIEL AND I
CAME UP WITH A PLAN.

28:50.649 --> 28:53.062
MY FATHER DIDN'T KNOW
WHAT HIT HIM.
 [ SIGHS ]

28:53.062 --> 28:54.273
DANIEL?

28:55.614 --> 28:57.316
ARE YOU SURE HE HAS
YOUR BEST INTERESTS AT HEART?

28:57.316 --> 29:00.199
I COULDN'T HAVE GOTTEN
MY MAGAZINE BACK WITHOUT HIM.

29:00.199 --> 29:03.572
HE'S NOT THE BAD PERSON
YOU THINK HE IS.

29:03.572 --> 29:05.124
YOU DON'T KNOW HIM.

29:05.124 --> 29:06.365
YES, I DO, JACK.

29:06.365 --> 29:08.367
WE'VE BEEN FRIENDS
SINCE WE WERE 10,

29:08.367 --> 29:10.960
WHICH IS LONGER THAN I CAN SAY
FOR YOU AND EMILY,

29:10.960 --> 29:13.332
WHO IT SEEMS HAS
QUITE THE REPUTATION HERSELF.

29:13.332 --> 29:15.754
TRUST ME. EMILY'S NOTHING LIKE
WHAT THE PAPERS ARE SAYING.

29:15.754 --> 29:18.047
MAYBE YOU'RE JUST BLINDED
BY YOUR FEELINGS FOR HER.

29:18.047 --> 29:19.718
WHAT ARE
YOU TALKING ABOUT?

29:19.718 --> 29:23.642
IS SHE WHY YOU'RE SO EAGER
FOR ME TO TAKE A JOB IN ITALY?

29:23.642 --> 29:25.885
OF COURSE NOT! WHY --
WHY WOULD YOU THINK
SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

29:27.807 --> 29:30.229
OKAY. [ CHUCKLES ]
FORGET IT.

29:30.229 --> 29:32.391
FORGET I SAID ANYTHING.
COME.

29:32.391 --> 29:34.193
COME CELEBRATE WITH ME.

29:34.193 --> 29:36.195
ARE YOU SURE?
 YES.

29:36.195 --> 29:40.569
ALL RIGHT, WELL, CARL COULD
USE A NEW PAIR OF SHOES.

29:40.569 --> 29:42.321
AND A COLLEGE FUND.
 [ CHUCKLES ]

29:44.453 --> 29:47.076
THERE SHE IS.
JUST IN TIME.

29:47.076 --> 29:49.869
I COULD USE SOME GOOD LUCK.
 OH, COME ON, MAN.

29:49.869 --> 29:51.460
JACK, IT'S FINE.

29:51.460 --> 29:53.462
COME ON!

29:53.462 --> 29:54.463
Woman: WHOO!

29:54.463 --> 29:56.465
[ ALL CHEERING ]
 YEAH!

30:00.920 --> 30:03.722
ONCE...

30:03.722 --> 30:06.555
I GAVE JACK UP,

30:06.555 --> 30:09.348
I WANTED TO
MAKE IT WORK WITH YOU.

30:09.348 --> 30:11.520
BUT I'D BEEN AWAY
FOR A YEAR,

30:11.520 --> 30:13.893
AND VICTORIA
HAD STOLEN YOU.

30:13.893 --> 30:18.487
SO I-I DIDN'T HAVE
MY HUSBAND

30:18.487 --> 30:20.069
OR MY SON,

30:20.069 --> 30:23.442
AND I JUST --
I FELL APART AGAIN.

30:26.825 --> 30:30.409
I HATED YOU
FOR LEAVING ME.

30:32.291 --> 30:35.454
BUT NOW I REALIZE
THAT I DROVE YOU AWAY.

30:37.336 --> 30:39.338
I LOVED YOU, STEPH.

30:41.460 --> 30:44.133
WE HAD OUR DEMONS --
MAYBE I STILL HAVE MINE --

30:44.133 --> 30:46.345
BUT WE HAD SOME...

30:46.345 --> 30:49.308
VERY GOOD YEARS
BEFORE THEY TOOK OVER.

30:50.849 --> 30:52.271
I KNOW.

30:52.271 --> 30:55.474
[ SIGHS ]

30:55.474 --> 30:58.477
I REGRET HAVING INVOLVED YOU
IN MY AFFAIRS YET AGAIN.

30:58.477 --> 31:01.650
IF THERE WAS ANY WAY
I COULD EXTRICATE YOU

31:01.650 --> 31:04.323
FROM THIS NEW BATTLE
WITH VICTORIA, I WOULD.

31:05.744 --> 31:07.406
NO GOOD CAN COME OF IT.

31:07.406 --> 31:10.409
TWO GOOD THINGS DID --

31:10.409 --> 31:11.870
JACK AND CARL.

31:14.994 --> 31:18.797
WHICH ONLY HIGHLIGHTS
OUR SEPARATE PATHS.

31:18.797 --> 31:22.211
[ SIGHS ]
I HOPE WE CAN MOVE ON.

31:22.211 --> 31:24.593
LEAVE THIS MESS
BEHIND US.

31:24.593 --> 31:27.056
I AGREE.

31:27.056 --> 31:29.638
WHEN ALL
IS SAID AND DONE,

31:29.638 --> 31:32.511
I AM TRULY HAPPY FOR YOU,
STEPH.

31:37.856 --> 31:39.648
[ SNIFFLES ]

31:39.648 --> 31:41.400
CONRAD, WAIT.

31:43.192 --> 31:44.443
[ SIGHS ]

31:44.443 --> 31:46.615
IT'S TIME
I PUT SOMETHING TO BED.

31:48.827 --> 31:53.412
PASCAL, YOU CAN GET
THE PAPERWORK STARTED, MON AMI.

31:53.412 --> 31:57.586
I'VE GOT VICTORIA'S TRUMP CARD.

31:57.586 --> 32:00.419
[ BEEP ]

32:02.671 --> 32:05.504
Pascal: THE LAST CARD.

32:05.504 --> 32:07.306
AND THE WINNER TONIGHT IS...

32:07.306 --> 32:10.009
MY CHARITY, OF COURSE.

32:10.009 --> 32:11.810
[ LAUGHTER AND APPLAUSE ]

32:11.810 --> 32:13.142
AND THE RIVER.

32:14.223 --> 32:15.604
QUEEN OF SPADES.

32:15.604 --> 32:17.396
THE BET IS TO MY LEFT.

32:26.615 --> 32:29.408
$120,000 TO YOU.

32:29.408 --> 32:31.620
OH, EMILY, I'M AFRAID
YOU'LL HAVE TO FOLD.

32:31.620 --> 32:33.452
YOU DON'T HAVE ENOUGH
TO MATCH THE BET.

32:42.791 --> 32:45.924
I THINK DANIEL'S
ENGAGEMENT RING SHOULD
BE ENOUGH TO COVER IT.

32:45.924 --> 32:47.086
[ CROWD GASPS ]

32:49.178 --> 32:51.050
I CALL.

32:51.050 --> 32:52.391
YOU'VE BEEN BLUFFING

32:52.391 --> 32:54.763
SINCE YOU SET FOOT
IN THE HAMPTONS. WHY STOP NOW?

32:54.763 --> 32:56.555
WELL, MAYBE I LIKE TO
TRY TO THROW YOU OFF YOUR GAME.

32:56.555 --> 32:58.057
CARDS, PLEASE.

33:00.519 --> 33:02.401
THREE QUEENS.

33:11.280 --> 33:14.283
FOR ONCE,
SHE WINS LEGITIMATELY.

33:14.283 --> 33:16.665
[ APPLAUSE ]

33:18.537 --> 33:20.459
SHALL WE SETTLE UP?

33:22.331 --> 33:23.502
YES.

33:37.015 --> 33:41.190
YOU HAVE QUITE AN IMPRESSIVE
POKER FACE, MISS THORNE.

33:41.190 --> 33:43.402
YOU'VE BEEN PLAYING ME
FROM THE START.

33:43.402 --> 33:45.484
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

33:45.484 --> 33:48.067
I THINK YOU'RE FAR SMARTER
THAN THE PUBLIC KNOWS.

33:48.067 --> 33:51.280
AND I BROUGHT YOU HERE
'CAUSE I BELIEVE

33:51.280 --> 33:54.453
YOUR INTEREST IN ME
IS ONLY PROFESSIONAL.

33:54.453 --> 33:57.326
IF I'M WRONG,
I'LL WISH YOU GOOD NIGHT.

33:57.326 --> 33:59.748
WELL, YOU CAUGHT ME.

34:04.793 --> 34:06.375
SO...

34:08.005 --> 34:11.429
...LET'S
GET DOWN TO BUSINESS.

34:11.429 --> 34:16.014
MY SHORT-LIVED MARRIAGE
TO DANIEL PROVIDED ME

34:16.014 --> 34:19.438
ACCESS TO THE GRAYSONS'
DEEPEST AND DARKEST SECRETS.

34:19.438 --> 34:21.560
AND YOU'RE
LOOKING TO CASH IN?

34:22.811 --> 34:26.024
SOMETHING LIKE THAT. PROVIDED
I CAN BE SURE YOU'RE AN ALLY.

34:26.024 --> 34:27.565
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:27.565 --> 34:29.447
AN INTRIGUING OFFER.

34:29.447 --> 34:32.070
I LIKE THAT.

34:32.070 --> 34:34.533
BUT WHY COME
TO A FRIEND OF CONRAD'S?

34:34.533 --> 34:38.157
BECAUSE YOU'RE FRIENDS SECOND,
COMPETITORS FIRST.

34:38.157 --> 34:39.658
AND I DON'T KNOW
ABOUT YOU,

34:39.658 --> 34:42.201
BUT I MAKE IT A POINT
TO COLLECT DIRT ON MY RIVALS.

34:42.201 --> 34:46.665
WE HAVE MORE IN COMMON
THAN I EXPECTED.

34:46.665 --> 34:48.337
[ CHUCKLES ]

34:51.049 --> 34:53.882
YOU'VE GOT A DEAL.

34:53.882 --> 34:57.676
[ STATIC INTERFERENCE ]

35:01.720 --> 35:04.102
SHOULD WE DISCUSS
DETAILS?

35:04.102 --> 35:05.984
PASCAL...

35:05.984 --> 35:09.148
I FEEL THAT I'VE PUT
A CONSIDERABLE AMOUNT OF ENERGY

35:09.148 --> 35:11.530
INTO GETTING
YOUR ATTENTION.

35:11.530 --> 35:14.283
AND NOW THAT I HAVE IT, I THINK
IT'S YOUR TURN TO GET MINE.

35:17.035 --> 35:19.328
THANK YOU FOR THE DRINK.

35:21.830 --> 35:25.043
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

35:25.043 --> 35:28.957
[ SIGHS ] HEY.

35:28.957 --> 35:31.880
I SENT THE SITTER HOME.
I HOPE IT'S OKAY.

35:31.880 --> 35:34.673
[ SIGHS ] OF COURSE.

35:34.673 --> 35:37.135
ACTUALLY, I'D RATHER SEE YOU
AFTER THE NIGHT I'VE HAD.

35:39.348 --> 35:40.849
WHAT ARE
YOU DOING HERE?

35:40.849 --> 35:43.222
I HAD A BIT
OF A TOUGH ONE, TOO.

35:44.853 --> 35:46.645
CONRAD CAME BY MY SUITE.

35:46.645 --> 35:48.437
WHAT DID HE DO?

35:48.437 --> 35:51.980
BELIEVE IT OR NOT...
HE JUST WANTED TO TALK.

35:51.980 --> 35:56.034
IT TOOK ME BACK TO A TIME
THAT I LEFT BEHIND

35:56.034 --> 35:56.985
LONG AGO.

35:56.985 --> 35:59.948
NOT AN EASY THING
TO RELIVE.

35:59.948 --> 36:03.332
I THOUGHT YOU SAID
YOUR MARRIAGE WASN'T ALL BAD.

36:03.332 --> 36:05.624
WHEN IT WAS BAD,
IT WAS HORRENDOUS.

36:05.624 --> 36:08.707
ESPECIALLY WHEN MY DRINKING
GOT OUT OF CONTROL.

36:08.707 --> 36:11.290
THE FIGHTS
WE USED TO GET INTO...

36:11.290 --> 36:13.712
[ SIGHS ]

36:13.712 --> 36:17.506
AND WHEN
THAT WOULD HAPPEN,

36:17.506 --> 36:21.099
THE ONLY THING
THAT WOULD GET ME THROUGH IT

36:21.099 --> 36:23.562
WAS A COUPLE DOZEN
DRINKS.

36:23.562 --> 36:26.975
SO...A-ARE YOU OKAY?

36:26.975 --> 36:28.857
I WILL BE.

36:30.188 --> 36:32.401
[ SIGHS ]

36:32.401 --> 36:34.653
I JUST NEED TO
GET A GOOD NIGHT'S REST.

36:34.653 --> 36:38.076
I'LL SEE YOU TOMORROW.
 OKAY.

36:40.699 --> 36:43.121
GOOD NIGHT.

36:43.121 --> 36:44.743
[ KAREN ELSON'S
"GOLD DUST WOMAN" PLAYS ]

36:50.629 --> 36:54.833
♪ ROCK ON, GOLD DUST WOMAN ♪

36:54.833 --> 36:57.836
♪ TAKE YOUR SILVER SPOON ♪

36:57.836 --> 37:01.049
♪ AND DIG YOUR GRAVE ♪

37:07.806 --> 37:10.979
♪ HEARTLESS CHALLENGE ♪

37:10.979 --> 37:15.193
♪ PICK YOUR PATH,
AND I'LL PRAY ♪

37:22.951 --> 37:26.164
♪ WAKE UP IN THE MORNING ♪

37:26.164 --> 37:28.997
♪ SEE YOUR SUNRISE ♪

37:28.997 --> 37:33.422
♪ LOVES TO GO DOWN ♪

37:34.583 --> 37:36.505
I RECEIVED YOUR GIFT.

37:36.505 --> 37:39.217
AND THIS ONE
I HAVEN'T COME TO RETURN.

37:42.090 --> 37:44.182
DARE I ASK
HOW YOU DID IT?

37:44.182 --> 37:46.144
AND SHOW MY HAND?
NEVER.

37:46.144 --> 37:48.477
JUST AS YOU DIDN'T
SHOW YOURS EARLIER.

37:48.477 --> 37:50.148
YOU LET EMILY WIN.

37:50.148 --> 37:52.891
I WANTED TO SEE HOW COMMITTED
SHE WAS TO HER NEXT MOVE.

37:52.891 --> 37:54.102
YOU'RE TRACKING HER.

37:54.102 --> 37:55.314
I'M HUNTING HER.

37:55.314 --> 37:57.155
♪ WELL, DID SHE MAKE YOU CRY? ♪

37:57.155 --> 37:59.318
THEN YOU'LL BE
INTERESTED TO KNOW

37:59.318 --> 38:02.901
THE ONLY THING
EMILY WANTED TO DISCUSS

38:02.901 --> 38:04.783
WAS YOUR FAMILY'S
SECRETS.

38:04.783 --> 38:06.535
♪ DO YOU KNOW HOW? ♪

38:06.535 --> 38:08.036
AND FOR YOU,
I WILL FIND OUT WHY.

38:08.036 --> 38:10.999
I'M GRATEFUL TO YOU,
PASCAL.

38:18.126 --> 38:21.920
DESPITE MY MARRIAGES,
MY DALLIANCES,

38:21.920 --> 38:25.013
I STILL REMEMBER
THE NIGHT I LOST YOU.

38:26.345 --> 38:30.559
♪ ROCK ON, ANCIENT QUEEN ♪

38:30.559 --> 38:33.772
♪ FOLLOW THOSE
WHO PALE IN YOUR SHADOW ♪
 [ CHUCKLES ]

38:33.772 --> 38:36.395
IT'S THE BLOND DRAGON.
MY FAVORITE.

38:37.396 --> 38:39.027
IT'S THOUGHT
TO BE EXTINCT.

38:39.027 --> 38:40.399
ALMOST.

38:41.860 --> 38:43.031
I'M SORRY.

38:43.031 --> 38:44.202
♪ RULERS MAKE BAD LOVERS ♪

38:44.202 --> 38:45.944
I WILL NEVER BETRAY
YOU AGAIN.

38:45.944 --> 38:48.577
♪ YOU BETTER PUT
YOUR KINGDOM UP FOR SALE ♪

38:48.577 --> 38:51.370
I KNOW THE STING OF BETRAYAL
ALL TOO WELL.

38:51.370 --> 38:56.124
AND I'M NOT ONE
TO FORGIVE FORGIVE AND FORGET.

38:58.627 --> 39:00.419
♪ WELL, DID SHE MAKE YOU CRY? ♪

39:00.419 --> 39:02.050
BUT I'M WILLING TO TRY.

39:02.050 --> 39:03.171
♪ MAKE YOU BREAK DOWN? ♪

39:03.171 --> 39:06.174
♪ SHATTER YOUR ILLUSIONS
OF LOVE? ♪

39:06.174 --> 39:09.017
♪ AND IS IT OVER NOW? ♪

39:09.017 --> 39:11.019
♪ DO YOU KNOW HOW ♪

39:11.019 --> 39:14.232
♪ TO PICK UP
THE PIECES AND GO HOME? ♪

39:14.232 --> 39:19.067
[ CHUCKLES ] SO...
PASCAL WAS NIXON'ing YOU?

39:19.067 --> 39:20.439
I KNEW THERE WAS
A CAMERA IN THE ROOM

39:20.439 --> 39:22.861
WHEN MY PHONE
PICKED UP INTERFERENCE.

39:22.861 --> 39:24.863
A CHEAP,
FRENCH IMITATION WhaleCam.

39:24.863 --> 39:26.114
WHILE I WAS
TRYING TO GET HIM TO TALK,

39:26.114 --> 39:28.156
HE WAS DOING THE SAME
TO ME -- ON TAPE.

39:28.156 --> 39:29.538
HMM. GUY'S GOOD.

39:29.538 --> 39:30.949
AND HE'S NOT
WORKING ALONE.

39:30.949 --> 39:32.791
LOOK,
I DON'T HAVE PROOF,

39:32.791 --> 39:35.994
BUT I'VE BEEN STUDYING
VICTORIA'S FACE FOR YEARS.

39:35.994 --> 39:38.126
SHE FOLDED THE WINNING HAND.
I'M SURE OF IT.

39:38.126 --> 39:40.669
WHAT, SO YOU'RE SAYING
THE QUEEN LOST ON PURPOSE?

39:40.669 --> 39:43.131
I THINK SHE WANTED ME
TO GET CLOSE TO PASCAL.

39:43.131 --> 39:45.964
WELL...

39:45.964 --> 39:48.967
THAT MEANS
FRENCHY'S A DEAD END.

39:48.967 --> 39:51.349
ALONG
WITH HIS MAINFRAME.

39:51.349 --> 39:54.352
I COMPLETED
MY "TWM" SEARCH

39:54.352 --> 39:58.777
AND CAME UP WITH...
NADA.

39:58.777 --> 40:03.191
I'M KIND OF SORT OF
OUT OF IDEAS.

40:06.945 --> 40:08.116
Aiden: I'VE GOT ONE.

40:11.159 --> 40:12.160
AIDEN.

40:12.160 --> 40:13.832
THIS ISN'T ABOUT YOU,
EMILY.

40:13.832 --> 40:15.874
IT'S ABOUT THIS.

40:15.874 --> 40:19.958
"TWM" IS
TREVOR WARREN MATHIS.

40:19.958 --> 40:23.802
PASCAL WAS TALKING
ABOUT MY FATHER.
